.Im MicroEmacs command
.so me.tni
.TH string-rectangle 3
.XI string-rectangle - "Add a string vertically"
.XI space-rectangle - "Adds space(s) vertically"
.SH NAME
.br
.Me "|string-rectangle"
string-rectangle \- Add a string vertically.
.br
.Me "|space-rectangle"
space-rectangle \- Adds space(s) vertically.
.Me $a
.SH SYNOPSIS
.na
.B string-rectangle
"\fIstring\fR"
.br
.I n
.B space-rectangle
.ad
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B string-rectangle
inserts  the  \fIstring\fR  at the same  column  position  on each line of the
current  region. The  command  prompts the user for a string and inserts it at
the  current  cursor  column on all the lines  between the cursor and the mark
inclusive. This is generally used to pre-pend lines with new text.
.PP
.B space-rectangle
is the  same as  \fBstring-rectangle\fR  except  it  inserts  \fIn\fR  spaces,
default being 1, rather than a given \fIstring\fR. This command is very useful
when moving a column of text over to align with another column.
